  "issue_title": "refactor: define local reasoning core boundary",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\n\nMilestone 2 needs a clean local reasoning core boundary. The app should clearly separate UI state, local command production, tool routing, policy checks, and Android execution.\n\nWithout this boundary, local model work, deterministic routing, skills, and safety policy will become tightly coupled and hard to test.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nDefine and implement the local reasoning core boundary:\n\n```text\nuser request + context\n  -> local reasoning core\n  -> agent events and/or structured tool request\n  -> tool router + policy\n  -> Android tool execution\n```\n\nThis should be an architecture cleanup with minimal behavior change.\n\n## User workflow\n\nExisting flows such as `Hello`, `Help`, `Open Settings`, and `Go back` should continue working, but internally they should pass through a clearer runtime boundary.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nThis keeps the core product independent from cloud providers and makes local command routing, local model reasoning, skills, and policy pluggable behind one local runtime boundary.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\nThe reasoning core must not execute tools directly. Tool execution must continue to go through validation, skill allowlists, policy, approvals, and logs.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Define the local reasoning core interface or module boundary.\n- [ ] UI does not directly own command production or Android tool execution.\n- [ ] Local router output can pass through the reasoning core boundary.\n- [ ] Tool execution remains behind tool router and policy checks.\n- [ ] Existing core flows still work.\n- [ ] Add focused unit tests for the boundary where practical.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-20T16:29:41.000Z",
